BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Love Letter to Handsome John (2026)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260529T200000
UID:260421NpEHuuWVIkGtR4LmLrfrtA
DESCRIPTION:After its Sold Out Premier in Indianapolis\, IN\, ***A Love L
 etter To Handsome John* (2026)** travels down the highway to Bloomington
  for a one-night only screening at The BCT.\n\nAn intimate portrait of **
 Todd Snider** in the last year of his life. What starts as a film about g
 ratitude\, and a way to say thank you to John Prine\, becomes a rare glimp
 se of the artist at home in his most quietest moments.\n\nMORE INFO: http
 s://otisgibbs.com/a-love-letter-to-handsome-john-by-otis-gibbs/\n\nRating:
  N/A Format: DCP Length: 54 Minutes\n\n**Filmaker Otis Gibbs** is a songw
 riter\, storyteller\, painter\, photographer\, and planter of 7\,176 trees
 . He once wrestled a bear and lost. He’s been called “the best unknown
  songwriter in music today\,” but if you ask him\, he’ll just say he
 ’s a folksinger.\n\n*The Trust Of Crows*\, his tenth studio album\, was 
 recorded at the iconic Columbia Studio A in Nashville\, where Bob Dylan ma
 de Blonde on Blonde and Nashville Skyline. It’s been closed to the publi
 c for decades\, but Otis was given permission to record there.\n\nGibbs’
  storytelling extends beyond music to his YouTube channel\, where more tha
 n 100\,000 subscribers listen to tales and folklore passed down by legenda
 ry musicians. In an effort to preserve these personal stories before they
 ’re lost to history\, he single handedly built a living archive in the s
 pirit of The Lomax Family\, Studs Terkel or even Charles Kuralt. This deep
 ly personal project reflects Otis’ reverence for history\, lived experie
 nce\, and the characters who shaped American roots music from the ground u
 p.\n\nOtis embraced a DIY ethic early on\, sometimes by choice and sometim
 es out of necessity. Whether it’s starting his own record label\, podcas
 t\, YouTube channel\, or whatever else needed to be done\, he’s created 
 his own ecosystem in the arts—all while wearing the same work shirt and 
 old felt hat that he wore planting trees 25 years ago. He continues to shi
 ne a light on the forgotten people\, places\, and the unvarnished beauty o
 f everyday life.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://buskirkchumley.org/events/a-love-letter-to-handsome-john-2026-
 may-29-2026/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Belt Out Loud! - Featuring Cody Ikerd and the Sidewinders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260530T203000
UID:2602030_C_r1IHN0yaOzBJPifhvg
DESCRIPTION:Stone Belt is proud to announce The Sixth Annual Belt Out Loud
 ! concert\, at 7pm on May 30th. This year’s headlining performers are co
 untry music stars **Cody Ikerd and the Sidewinders**\, whose heartfelt son
 gs and captivating stage presence promise an unforgettable evening.\n\nAtt
 endees can enjoy a night of incredible music while supporting a great caus
 e. Belt Out Loud serves as a model for future events aiming to promote acc
 essibility and inclusion for individuals of all abilities\, ensuring an en
 joyable experience for everyone. By supporting Belt Out Loud\, attendees a
 re advocating for a more inclusive society and promoting awareness about t
 he importance of accessibility. Together\, we’ll enjoy a night of music 
 and pave the way for a future where every event\, big or small\, embraces 
 inclusivity as it’s core value.\n\nThe proceeds from the event will help
  Stone Belt provide vital services to individuals with developmental disab
 ilities in our community\, including employment training\, day and residen
 tial services\, and advocacy support. So come out and enjoy a fantastic co
 ncert while making a positive impact!\n\n**This event is proudly sponsored
  by IU Credit Union\, Old National Bank\, Office Easel\, Tri-County Hydrau
 llics\, Resource Services\, and Visit Bloomington.**\n\nThe proceeds from 
 your ticket will help Stone Belt provide vital services to individuals wit
 h developmental disabilities in our community\, including employment train
 ing\, day and residential services\, and advocacy support. So come out and
  enjoy a fantastic concert while making a positive impact!
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://buskirkchumley.org/events/belt-out-loud-featuring-cody-ikerd-a
 nd-the-sidewinders-may-30-2026/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
