BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Another Revolution
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260613T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260613T193000
UID:250915UQVkkUfocU-no4myoACWMg
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Another Revolution\,
 ” on stage June 4-21 at the Constellation Playhouse. \n\n***Some revolu
 tions happen in the streets. Others in the lab.***\n\nKat and Henry\, two 
 graduate students from opposing scientific disciplines\, are forced to sha
 re a lab at Columbia University in 1968. Amidst interpersonal differences\
 , a campus devolving into political chaos\, and the uncertainty and turmoi
 l of the outside world\, they each discover what it’s like to be thrown 
 into someone else’s orbit. *By Jacqueline Bircher\, playwright of Conste
 llation’s hit production of* Webster’s B!+@#. *Recommended for ages 13
 +.*\n\nSee Constellation’s website for more information\, including a de
 tailed performance schedule. Learn more and find tickets at https://seecon
 stellation.org/mainstage/another-revolution/
LOCATION:Constellation Playhouse
URL:https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/another-revolution/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
